{{TODO|todonote=Finish! Add history, kernel details, and explanations distributions that use it. Brief install/use help is probably good.|A Neutral Look at Operating Systems}} '''GNU Hurd''' is an operating system based on the GNU Hurd kernel. It is intended to supplement the GNU userspace utilities. Currently there are only a limited number of distributions that include it as the kernel, as it is not ready for production. It is built on top of a microkernel, GNU Mach, with daemons running on top of it.
== Distributions that include Hurd == There are versions of the Arch and Debian operating systems that use the Hurd kernel instead of the Linux kernel.
