== Introduction to Computer Science == === Christian Brothers Academy === :[[Main Page]] ;Network Concepts ;HTML and Web Pages ;Advanced HTML ;CSS: Cascading Style Sheets ;Counting and Number Systems ;Boolean Logic ;A Brief History of Computer Technology ;Introduction to Programming
[[Category:Collections|Introduction to Computer Science]]

{{book title|Introduction To Business}}
The mission of this book is to provide students with a basic understanding of the many different aspects in business.
===Table of Contents=== #[[/Overview/]] #[[/Economics/]] #[[/Accounting and Financial Statements/]] #[[/Finance Basics/]] #[[/Management/]] #[[/Human Resource Management/]] #[[/Production and Operations Management/]] #[[/Marketing/]] #[[/Global Business/]] #[[/Ethics/]] #[[/Personal Finances/]]
{{alphabetical|I}} {{subjects|Business}} {{status|0%}}

{{Logic_IC |number = 4007 |logic_type = Transistor-level |func_family = Transistor |description = Dual complementary pair and inverter |pins = 14 }}
The 4007 integrated circuit contains three complementary enhancement-mode [[:en:MOSFET|MOSFET]] pairs. One pair has connections to the drain terminals, one to the source terminals and the commonned drains (i.e. it is wired as an inverter) and one allows access to all source and drain connections. All pairs have the gate terminals commonned and available. The bulk connections are to the power rails (V<sub>DD</sub> for the p-channel devices and V<sub>SS</sub> for the n-channel devices).
The meanings of the abbreviations on the diagrams to the right are: {|class=wikitable style="margin: 1em auto 1em auto" !width=80|Pins!!Functions |- |S<sub>P2</sub>, S<sub>P3</sub> || Source terminals of 2nd and 3rd p-channel MOSFETs |- |D<sub>P1</sub>, D<sub>P2</sub> || Drain terminals of 1st and 2nd p-channel MOSFETs |- |D<sub>N1</sub>, D<sub>N2</sub> || Drain terminals of 1st and 2nd n-channel MOSFETs |- |S<sub>N2</sub>, S<sub>N3</sub> || Source terminals of 2nd and 3rd n-channel MOSFETs |- |D<sub>3</sub> || Drain terminals (common) of 3rd p-channel and n-channel MOSFETs |- |G<sub>1</sub>, G<sub>2</sub>, G<sub>3</sub> || Gate terminals of each MOSFET pair. |} [[Category:Practical Electronics]]

